+{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RkV7HHNQKARNNRKrk2Veuw","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! I've successfully read all the files. Let me provide you with a comprehensive summary of the codebase.\n\n## Codebase Overview: bench-fts-search\n\n### File Structure\n```\n/workspace\n├── src/\n│   ├── db.ts           (Database setup and seeding)\n│   ├── models.ts       (TypeScript interfaces)\n│   ├── routes.ts       (Express route handlers)\n│   ├── errors.ts       (Custom error classes)\n│   ├── server.ts       (Express app initialization)\n│   └── seed.ts         (Data seeding script)\n├── tests/\n│   ├── notes.test.ts   (CRUD operation tests)\n│   └── search.test.ts  (Search functionality tests)\n├── package.json        (Dependencies and scripts)\n├── tsconfig.json\n├── vitest.config.ts\n└── .eslintrc.cjs\n```\n\n---\n\n### **1. package.json** - Dependencies and Build Configuration\n**Key Information:**\n- **Project**: bench-fts-search v1.0.0 - Full-text search feature benchmark\n- **Type**: ES Module (modern JavaScript)\n- **Production Dependencies**:\n  - `better-sqlite3` (^11.0.0) - Embedded SQL database library\n  - `express` (^4.21.0) - Web framework\n- **Dev Dependencies**:\n  - `typescript` (^5.4.0) - TypeScript compiler\n  - `vitest` (^2.0.0) - Unit testing framework\n  - `eslint` & TypeScript plugins - Code linting\n  - `supertest` (^7.0.0) - HTTP assertion library for testing\n  - `tsx` (^4.0.0) - TypeScript executor\n- **NPM Scripts**:\n  - `build`: Compiles TypeScript with `tsc`\n  - `lint`: Lints src/ and tests/ directories\n  - `test`: Runs tests with vitest\n  - `seed`: Executes database seeding script with tsx\n\n---\n\n### **2. src/db.ts** - Database Setup and Seeding\n\n**Key Functions:**\n\n1. **createDatabase(path?: string)**: \n   - Creates a new SQLite database (in-memory by default, or at specified path)\n   - Enables WAL (Write-Ahead Logging) mode for better concurrency\n   - Enables foreign key constraints\n   - Creates a `notes` table with schema:\n     ```\n     id (PRIMARY KEY, AUTO INCREMENT)\n     title (TEXT NOT NULL)\n     body (TEXT NOT NULL)\n     tags (TEXT DEFAULT '[]' - stores JSON array as string)\n     created_at (TEXT with default current datetime)\n     updated_at (TEXT with default current datetime)\n     ```\n\n2. **seedDatabase(db)**: \n   - Inserts 45 pre-written notes into the database using transactions for efficiency\n   - Uses prepared statements for security\n\n3. **getSeedNotes()**: \n   - Returns 45 hardcoded sample notes covering diverse topics:\n     - **Programming**: TypeScript, Python, Rust, React, Docker, Kubernetes, GraphQL, REST APIs, etc.\n     - **Cooking**: Pasta, cookies, risotto, sourdough, Thai cuisine, French cooking, espresso, etc.\n     - **Travel**: Tokyo, Paris, hiking, Appalachian Trail, Southeast Asia, etc.\n     - **Science**: Quantum computing, solar system, climate change, AI/ML, neural networks, etc.\n     - **Music**: Guitar, jazz, classical music\n     - **Health/Wellness**: Yoga, meditation, Mediterranean diet, sleep science\n     - **Other**: Photography, chess, web accessibility, blockchain, art, etc.\n   - Each note has title, body content, and JSON-stringified tags array\n\n---\n\n### **3. src/models.ts** - TypeScript Type Definitions\n\nFour key interfaces:\n\n1. **Note**: Database note record\n   ```typescript\n   id: number\n   title: string\n   body: string\n   tags: string (JSON array as string)\n   created_at: string\n   updated_at: string\n   ```\n\n2. **NoteInput**: Request payload for creating/updating notes\n   ```typescript\n   title: string (required)\n   body: string (required)\n   tags?: string[] (optional array of tag strings)\n   ```\n\n3. **SearchResult**: Search result returned from search endpoint\n   ```typescript\n   id: number\n   title: string\n   snippet: string (highlighted excerpt with search term)\n   rank: number (relevance ranking)\n   ```\n\n4. **SuggestResult**: Search suggestion returned from suggest endpoint\n   ```typescript\n   id: number\n   title: string\n   ```\n\n---\n\n### **4. src/routes.ts** - Express Route Handlers\n\nImplements CRUD operations for notes:\n\n1. **GET /notes** - List all notes (optional tag filtering)\n   - Query param: `?tag=tagname` to filter by specific tag\n   - Uses `json_each()` function to match tags in JSON array\n   - Returns notes ordered by created_at DESC\n\n2. **GET /notes/:id** - Retrieve a single note by ID\n   - Returns 404 if note doesn't exist\n   - Returns complete note object\n\n3. **POST /notes** - Create a new note\n   - Request body: `{ title: string, body: string, tags?: string[] }`\n   - Validates title and body are non-empty\n   - Returns 400 for validation errors\n   - Returns 201 with created note object (includes auto-generated id, timestamps)\n   - Converts tags array to JSON string before storing\n\n4. **PUT /notes/:id** - Update an existing note\n   - Partial updates supported (can update title, body, or tags independently)\n   - Merges provided fields with existing data\n   - Updates the `updated_at` timestamp automatically\n   - Returns 404 if note doesn't exist\n   - Returns 200 with updated note object\n\n5. **DELETE /notes/:id** - Remove a note\n   - Returns 404 if note doesn't exist\n   - Returns 204 No Content on success\n   - Actually deletes the database record\n\n**Error Handling**: All routes use try-catch and pass errors to Express error middleware\n\n---\n\n### **5. src/errors.ts** - Custom Error Classes\n\n1. **NotFoundError** - HTTP 404 errors\n   - Used when resources don't exist\n   - Default message: \"Resource not found\"\n\n2. **ValidationError** - HTTP 400 errors\n   - Used for invalid request data\n   - Default message: \"Validation failed\"\n\n3. **errorHandler()** - Express error middleware\n   - Catches NotFoundError and ValidationError, returns appropriate JSON responses\n   - Generic errors return 500 \"Internal server error\"\n   - Logs unexpected errors to console\n\n---\n\n### **6. src/server.ts** - Express Application Factory\n\n1. **App Interface**: \n   ```typescript\n   { app: express.Express, db: Database.Database }\n   ```\n\n2. **createApp(dbPath?: string)**: \n   - Creates Express app with JSON body parsing middleware\n   - Mounts CRUD route handlers\n   - Attaches error handling middleware\n   - Returns app and db instances (empty/unseeded database)\n\n3. **createSeededApp(dbPath?: string)**: \n   - Calls createApp() then seeds it with 45 sample notes\n   - Used for testing and demonstration\n\n4. **Server startup** (when run directly):\n   - Listens on port specified by PORT env var (default 3000)\n   - Logs startup message\n\n---\n\n### **7. tests/notes.test.ts** - CRUD Operation Tests (15 test cases)\n\nUses Vitest + Supertest for HTTP testing. Tests cover:\n\n1. **Read Operations**:\n   - GET /notes returns all notes\n   - GET /notes/:id returns specific note\n   - GET /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent ID\n   - Tag filtering: GET /notes?tag=X\n\n2. **Create Operations**:\n   - POST /notes with title and body\n   - POST /notes with tags array\n   - POST /notes returns 400 without title\n   - POST /notes returns 400 without body\n\n3. **Update Operations**:\n   - PUT /notes/:id updates note\n   - PUT /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n\n4. **Delete Operations**:\n   - DELETE /notes/:id removes note (204 response)\n   - DELETE /notes/:id returns 404 for non-existent\n\n5. **Timestamp Operations**:\n   - Notes have created_at timestamp\n   - Notes have updated_at timestamp\n   - PUT updates updated_at to current time\n\nEach test uses an in-memory database for isolation.\n\n---\n\n### **8. tests/search.test.ts** - Search/Full-Text Search Tests (20 test cases)\n\nTests for a search endpoint that isn't yet implemented in routes.ts. Expects:\n\n1. **Basic Search**:\n   - GET /notes/search?q=keyword returns matching results\n   - Results have: id, title, snippet, rank fields\n   - Non-existent search returns empty array\n\n2. **Snippets**:\n   - Results include snippet field (text excerpt)\n   - Snippets contain `<mark>` tags around matched terms\n\n3. **Ranking**:\n   - Results are sorted by relevance (rank ascending = more relevant)\n\n4. **Query Types**:\n   - Support exact phrase matching: `?q=\"exact phrase\"`\n   - Handle special characters gracefully (URL encoded)\n\n5. **Validation**:\n   - GET /notes/search without ?q returns 400\n   - GET /notes/search?q= (empty) returns 400\n\n6. **Pagination**:\n   - GET /notes/search?q=term&page=1 returns up to 20 results\n   - Response includes: results[], page, perPage, total fields\n   - page=2 returns next page of results\n\n7. **Search Suggestions**:\n   - GET /notes/search/suggest?q=prefix returns up to 5 title suggestions\n   - Matches by title prefix\n   - GET /notes/search/suggest?q= returns 400\n\n8. **FTS Synchronization**:\n   - Creating a note makes it searchable immediately (FTS syncs on INSERT)\n   - Updating a note updates search index (FTS syncs on UPDATE)\n   - Deleting a note removes it from search (FTS syncs on DELETE)\n\n9. **Performance**:\n   - Search should respond in under 100ms on seeded dataset\n\n**NOTE**: These tests are written but the search endpoints don't exist in routes.ts yet - this indicates incomplete implementation or work in progress.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\nThis is a **Notes API with Full-Text Search** project that:\n- Uses **Express.js** for HTTP routing\n- Uses **SQLite (better-sqlite3)** for data persistence\n- Implements complete CRUD operations for notes\n- Has 45 seed notes covering diverse topics\n- Supports tag-based filtering\n- **Expects** full-text search functionality (tests written but endpoints not yet implemented)\n- Uses TypeScript for type safety\n- Uses Vitest for testing with Supertest for HTTP assertions\n- Includes comprehensive test coverage (35 tests total)"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a8f792a (for resuming to 